items.title: U.S. Supreme Court temporarily halts deportations of Venezuelan migrants under wartime law
items.description: The U.S. Supreme Court early on Saturday paused President Donald Trump's administration from deporting Venezuelan men in immigration custody.

items.title: Iran, U.S. to hold talks in Rome in bid to reach nuclear deal
items.description: Iran and the United States will hold a new round of nuclear talks in Rome on Saturday to resolve their decades-long standoff over Tehran's atomic aims...

items.title: Trump to reclassify many federal workers, making them easier to fire
items.description: Trump to reclassify many federal workers, making them easier to fire.

items.title: U.S. judge temporarily blocks mass firings at consumer bureau
items.description: A federal judge on Friday halted the mass firings carried out Thursday afternoon at the U.S. Consumer Financial Protection Bureau.

items.title: Trump will study whether to fire Fed Chair Powell, adviser says
items.description: "The president and his team will continue to study that matter," the White House economic adviser said.
